Road Accident Analysis In UK¶

18.03.2021¶

Introduction¶

Accidents are events that are unfortunate, occur unexpectedly and unintentionally due to several variables, and result in damage to individuals and property. Such unplanned events can be prevented if circumstances and problems for possible outcomes can be recognized beforehand and effective counter measures taken to prevent it or reduce the impact of its occurrence.The aim of my analysis is to understand patterns of personal injury road accidents and the relation between the accident and different demographic conditions like weather, road type, Road surface condition etc. The growth in countries' economies and populations has caused a rise in various externalities, like the increase of road crashes. There are millions of deaths from traffic accidents every year, besides severe social, and environmental consequences. In the UK itself every year more than 1500 people died in road collision incidents according to the report published by UK police, Many efforts have been made to reduce the frequency and severity of traffic accidents but still, the incidents were rising. There are so many factors that contribute to these accidents like lighting, weather, road surface conditions, road type, Driving speed, drink driving rates, etc. My aim is to analyze these Factors, by mapping the data to explore the pattern of accident conditions across the country and to see if there is any relationship that I can find between environmental conditions and the rate of accidents.

The Dataset provide detailed road safety statistic about the circumstances of personal injury road accidents in the UK, the types of vehicles involved and the consequential casualties. my aim is to relate the accidents on public roads that have been reported to the police, and recorded using the STATS19 accident reporting form. The files I have chosen to work with span the years 2016 to 2019.The Dataset is very wide, there is a scope of lot's of analysis can be done on this, so in my analysis, I will use some interactive plots like a bar, scatter, the line to represent the insight of the data, also I will build some table for the customization of the factor to see their individual impact, apart from this I will build a time series model on the casualties to analyze the past trend and seasonality and will predict the future casualties for next 12 month.

The dataset for this analysis is available in the UK police government website the link of which is as follows (https://data.gov.uk/dataset/cb7ae6f0-4be6-4935-9277-47e5ce24a11f/road-safety-data). From this site i took dataset between 2016 to 2019.

Dataset Detail¶

  • The Accident dataset contains the records of Accident ID, Police Force District, date of the accident, Number of vehicles involved in an accident, casualty, Speed limit, road type, weather condition, light condition, etc. there is a total of 32 variables present inside this some of which I will try to eliminate in my further calculation based on the availability of my model.
  • Vehicle Dataset contains the details about the types of vehicle, age of the driver,sex of the driver,Point of impact during accident,Age of the vehicle.There arre total 22 attributes present inside this dataset.
  • Casualty Dataset is one of the most important dataset because it contains the detail about the Sex of casualty,Age of Casualty,Caualty type,Casualty Severity,Car or Bus Passenger location at the time of accident.There are total 16 attributes present in this dataset.
  • All the dataset have one common column Accident Index,which contains the id of each reported accident,i will use this at the time of joining these three dataset.

Time Series Analysis,

Time series analysis is the process of making predictions based on past and present data and most commonly by analysis of seasonalty, levels and trends. Here i will use this technique to predict the future accident numbers based on previous trends.By analyzing the values of last 4 years i will build a forecast model and based on the accuracy i will predict the future value for next 12 month.

For that i will consider only Accident dataset of last 4 years becuase casualty column lies on it,then i will transform my index into date and then summarize the casualties in month instead of day wise frequency.

Time Series Plot Analysis¶

There is some seasonalty(Shows the mean value of the series that remains constant over a time period; if past effects accumulate and the values increase toward infinity) present in the data as the oeak and low is reported on particular month and there is a pattern between these, also the trend is negative here, the caualty cases were reducing over the time.I can say this is an example of multiplicative seasonal changes, the magnitude of the seasonal change decreases over time as the casualties values increase.

#Define MAPE(Mean Absolute Percentage Error) for error calculation
def MAPE(pred,org):
    Error = np.abs((pred-org)/org)*100
    return np.mean(Error)

Exponential Smoothing¶

This method predicts the one next period value based on the past and current value. It involves averaging of data such that the nonsystematic components of each individual case or observation cancel out each other. The exponential smoothing method is used to predict the short term predication. Alpha, Gamma, Phi, and Delta are the parameters that estimate the effect of the time series data. Alpha is used when seasonality is not present in data. Gamma is used when a series has a trend in data. Delta is used when seasonality cycles are present in data. A model is applied according to the pattern of the data. After analyzing all the three method i got the minimum error in case of exponential smoothing, so next i build my final model on this method and will pass last 4 years values into it and predict for next 12 month.

In [ ]:
fitted_model = ExponentialSmoothing(Accident_data['Number_of_Casualties'],trend='mul',
                                    seasonal= 'mul',seasonal_periods=12).fit()

test_predictions = fitted_model.forecast(24)

plt.figure(figsize=(10, 8))
plt.title('Current and forecasted Number of Casualties using Holt Winters')
Accident_data['Number_of_Casualties'].plot(legend=True,label='Current')
test_predictions.plot(legend=True,label='PREDICTION')

Preprocessing the data¶

Final_Data2 = Final_Data.copy()

Most of the columns present in the dataset were categorical,and they were represent by numbers, For the EDA i have to transform it into their respective text, so that at the time of visualiztion it's easy for me to understand and intrepret meaning from them.For that i will create the list for each attribute according to their respected number and then map it to the column.

Vehicle_dict = {1:'Pedal Cycle',2:'Motorcycle 50cc',3:'Motorcycle 125cc',4:'Motorcycle 500cc',5:'Motorcycle over 500cc',8:'Taxi',9:'Car',10:'Minibus',
                11:'Bus',16:'Ridden Horse',17:'Agricultural Vehicle',18:'Tram',19:'Van/Goods 3.5T',20:'Goods 3.5T-7.5T',21:'Goods > 7.5T',
                22:'Mobility Scooter',23:'Electric Motorcycle',90:'Other',97:'Other',98:'Other',-1:'Other'}
Class_dict = {1:'Driver',2:'Passenger',3:'Pedestrian'}
Sex_dict = {1:'Male',2:'Female',-1:'Unknown'}
Left_drive = {1:'No',2:'Yes',-1:'Unknown'}
Skiding_dict = {0:'None',1:'Skidded',2:'Skidded and OverTurned',3:'Jackknifed',4:'Jackknifed and Overturned',5:'Overturned',-1:'Unknown'}
Severity_dict = {1: "Fatal", 2 : "Serious", 3 : "Light"}
Day_dict = {1: 'Sunday', 2 : 'Monday', 3 : 'Tuesday', 4 : "Wednesday", 5 : 'Thursday', 6 : "Friday", 7 : 'Saturday'}

                7:'Fog',8:'Other',9:'Other',-1:'Other'}
Road_dict = {1:'Dry',2:'Wet or Dump',3:'Snow',4:'Frost or Ice',5:'Flood',6:'Oil',7:'Mud',-1:'Other'}

EDA Takeways¶

  • As the number of casualty decrease in these years the maximum decline record in the light injuries, all three types of injury shows negative trend but the Light cases injuries reduced significantly.
  • Most of the casualty cases happened with the individual who was out for an unknown reason, or just roaming around the town, the next section who suffered most casualty was the office going person or person who was out for work, it may ve delivery guys. The lowest case was recorded in the case of the pupil. If I talk about the days of the week there is no much difference between them, almost the number of the casualty was same for all the days, where Friday record most number of casualties.
  • As the light condition is also an important factor, Most of the accidents have occurred in the daylight and the lowest in darkness. Also the cases of an accident in darkness were reduced compared to 2016, the reason behind that may be the street light were installed in those areas.
  • The maximum Accident was happened with the car rider, as it accounts for more than 85 percent of total cases. The reason behind this may be distracted drivers(like eating, reading, and putting on makeup), Speeding, Alcohol, and Drug-Induced Drivers, Weather Conditions. In these car accidents, almost 60 percent of the time the casualty happened to the driver.
  • sex is also a significant factor in accidents as male counts were high compare to female indulge in an accident.
  • More than 50 percent of the accident have happened in the zone where the speed limit is 30 MPH, and that's the reason behind why most of the casualty were light, there are some cases in the speed limit range of 60 to 70 Mph but those were also reducing after 2016 significantly.
  • Dry Road surface conditions had more accidents in last 4 years compared to wet and flood road,This could be due to the events of snowing being less likely and frequent in comparison to Dry or wet surfaces and could also be attributed to experiencing more period of warmer drier weather due to the effects of global warming. If however, the amount of days were kept same for all three types of road surfaces under investigation, ice could have a greatest percentage due to added risk brought by the ice/snowy surface such as skidding due to lack of grip for vehicles making manoeuvring hard which could lead to crash along with braking. Although aware, this makes an individual in a vehicle helpless when put under the situation.

Conclusion¶

My main agenda behind this analysis was to see a pattern between the factor for road accident and to see if the recording of these data makes any changes to the casualty, and I can say that yes there is a significant change in the number of casualties and also the factor which contributed more in the previous year reduced significantly in coming years. there is some factor which directly related to the number of casualty like types of passenger(Most of the accident reported were of car passenger ), local area type(the number of the accident were more in case of urban compare to the rural area), in the same way, the speed limit is directly related to the urban area because the speed limit was high in case of the rural area compared to an urban area. Friday has the highest amount of accidents so far, but there is not a big gap between Friday and other days, and accidents usually take place in the afternoon, on-peak hours, when people usually go out and come back home after school and work. Accidents with Slight severity occurred the most and usually be in an urban area. Average drivers ages are 25–45, mostly male. Light, weather, and road surface do not matter much according to the graphs but do remember that the number of accidents has occurred more during the normal conditions (people tend to drive more in a safe environment). Solutions to reduce the number of accidents are promote improvement in driver behavior, set road safety rules, maintain and improve safety features in cars, improve public transportation systems, improve road environments, make use of technology and data to prevent the accident, cancel lifelong-license, and create two-way benefit campaigns. The record of these data was really helpful because it will make us understand the factor behind the accident and in the future, we can reduce these accidents by eliminating those factors directly or improving the condition.
